Overview of computer networks       “Everything happens over a network”

Computer network = group of devices when connected to each other allow them to share information and resources


Essential devices that make up a network: SWITCHES , ROUTERS , FIREWALLS 

- Switches = "manager for your local party network keeping things tidy “ ( local )
-  it connects the multiple devices in the LAN + ensures smooth data flow ( no congestion + communication)

- Routers : “traffic cops for network and a route to connect to the internet” (wide)
- Directs traffic between different networks/ LAN’s -  I.e your home wifi to the internet 

- Firewalls = " Security guard for ur network”
- Protects network against unauthorised access 
- Monitors incoming and outgoing network traffic + Based no predetermined security rules 



Different types of computer networks include : 

- Local area network (LAN) = small + provides internet access + connects devices to share resources - covers limited area 
- Wide area network (WAN) = Large area (city/country) + connects multiple LAN’s = facilitating resource sharing + data transfer for far distances 
