IP Addresses & Mac Address.   “Without IP address , devices wouldn’t know where to send and receive data”

Devices have 2 unique identifiers as an ip address and a MAC address :
IP address is unique identifier for devices changing depending on what network your on 
MAC address is a unique identifier that is permanent and doesn’t change regardless of network 


? Types of IP Addresses 
- IPV4 = 32 bit + 4 decimal numbers and becoming outdated 
- IPV6 = 128 bit + 4 groups of hexadecimal digits separated with colons + provides more address + better security + simplified addresses assignment 


? IP Address ( internet protocol address) = unique identifier/number given to each devices on a network 
- Allows devices to locate + communicate with each other 
- Helps the data know where to go and how to get back to u 
- USE CASES = where to send and receive data , identify which device is causing an issue on a network 


? MAC address = operates at the data link layer 
- Facilitates devices identifier within a local network 
- Essential for network communication and security 
- USE CASES = MAC address filtering (to connect to ur router) , identifier for which hardware in trouble 



Intro to ports and protocols 

? Ports = 2 way door for data in a network - flows in and out - but only certain type of info can be used certain ports 
- Neat way to organise that kind of traffic goes where 
- I.e web traffic usually comes in thru port 80 for HTTP
 
Protocols = the rules for the data on how its formatted and transmitted across a network 

pports + protocols = ports make sure the data gets to the right application on ur device and protocol make sure the data is formatted right and is understandable + formatted = communication 

? Types of protocols? TCP VS UDP 

TCP = Transmission control protocol “careful planner”
- Connection oriented
- Send everything in order and anything lost it resends so nothing gets lost + error checks , flow control + bidirectional flow 

- USE CASES = web browsing you need inn the right order , file transfer , emails , reliability 


UDP =
- One way traffic 
- Simple protocol to send & receive data 
- Prior communication not needed 
- Fast and don’t care if a little data gets lost 

- USE CASES = suitable for real time video streaming , DNS , VPN 
